up()"},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"attribute","text":"nonisolated"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"geometryGroup"},{"kind":"text","text":"() -> "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"some"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore4ViewP","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/View","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"View"},{"kind":"text","text":"\n"}],"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"text":"Discussion","anchor":"discussion","type":"heading","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"By default OpenSwiftUI views push position and size changes down"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"through the view hierarchy, so that only views that draw"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"something (known as leaf views) apply the current animation to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"their frame rectangle. However in some cases this coalescing"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"behavior can give undesirable results; inserting a geometry"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"group can correct that. A group acts as a barrier between the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"parent view and its subviews, forcing the position and size"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"values to be resolved and animated by the parent, before being"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"passed down to each subview."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The example below shows one use of this function: ensuring that","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the member views of each row in the stack apply (and animate","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"as) a single geometric transform from their ancestor view,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"rather than letting the effects of the ancestor views be","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"applied separately to each leaf view. If the members of","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"ItemView","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" may be added and removed at different times the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"group ensures that they stay locked together as animations are"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"applied."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["VStack {","    ForEach(items) { item in","        ItemView(item: item)","            .geometryGroup()","    }","}"]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Returns: a new view whose geometry is isolated from that of its"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"parent view."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/openswiftui\/labeledcontentstyleconfiguration\/content-swift.struct\/geometrygroup()"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"references":{"doc://OpenSwiftUI/documentation/OpenSwiftUI/LabeledContentStyleConfiguration/Content-swift.struct/geometryGroup()":{"type":"topic","role":"symbol","kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"text":"Isolates the geometry (e.g. position and size) of the view","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"from its parent view.","type":"text"}],"url":"\/documentation\/openswiftui\/labeledcontentstyleconfiguration\/content-swift.struct\/geometrygroup()","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"geometryGroup","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"() -> ","kind":"text"},{"text":"some","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"View","preciseIdentifier":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore4ViewP","kind":"typeIdentifier"}],"title":"geometryGroup()","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/LabeledContentStyleConfiguration\/Content-swift.struct\